<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="288" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,548,1439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,620,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2019" box="[1026,1152,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Promalactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bigeminata">
<emphasis box="[1026,1152,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">bigeminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the uncus widened triangularly from distal 1/4 to a straight apex, and the valva produced distally to a beak-like process. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Liu, 2019" authorityName="Wang &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2019" box="[264,463,694,719]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Promalactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventericoncava" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[264,463,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">P. ventericoncava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[469,559,693,719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[469,559,693,719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="288" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the shape of the male genitalia, and the differences between them are stated in the diagnosis of the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="288" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,548,1439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,764,791]" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[427,496,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 1‒7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1805,1830]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,174,1786]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,174,1786]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1‒7. Adults of Promalactis spp. 1, P. bigeminata sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 2, P. derecta sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 3, P. pectinacea sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 4, P. pileata sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 5, P. scalpelliformis sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 6, P. ventericoncava sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 7, P. venteriprocessa sp. nov., paratype, ♀; 7b, head. Scales = 2 mm except 7b = 0.2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772547" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772547/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 8.0 mm. Head white, occiput pale brownish yellow. Labial palpus white, second segment with basal 3/4 yellow on outer surface, third segment with distal 1/3 black. Antenna with scape white except black apically on dorsal surface; flagellum white annulated with black on dorsal surface, white and dark brown on ventral surface. Collar, thorax and tegula pale brownish yellow; thorax white posteriorly. Forewing orange yellow; three white fasciae margined with sparse blackish-brown scales: basal fascia at proximal base; antemedian fascia running from about basal 1/5 of costal margin to middle of dorsum, oblique outward, widened anteriorly; postmedian fascia from basal 3/5 of costal margin directly to dorsum before tornus, anterior half enlarged sub-quadrately, posterior half sub-triangular, with dense grey scales on outer margin; apical spot white, ovate, margined with black scales; termen with dense black scales, interrupted with white scales; cilia orange yellow, mixed with black-tipped scales. Hindwing and cilia grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,548,1439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[378,447,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 8‒11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1720,1745]" captionTargetBox="[173,1425,569,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,553,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 8‒11. Male genitalia of Promalactis spp. 8, P. bigeminata sp. nov., paratype, slide No. DZH10321; 9, P. derecta sp. nov., holotype, slide No. DZH09023; 10, P. pectinacea sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZMUC-NK019; 11, P. pileata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. DZH09007. Scales = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772549" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772549/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Uncus slightly narrowed medially, suddenly widened from distal 1/4 to straight apex. Tegumen gradually narrowed anteriorly. Valva sub-rectangular, produced distally to a beak-like process pointing ventrad; costa with basal half sclerotized, distal half sparsely setose. Sacculus narrow, densely setose distally. Saccus narrow, rounded apically, slightly longer than uncus. Juxta weakly sclerotized, folded inward and forming a wide ring; anterior lobe slender. Aedeagus slightly longer than valva, slightly curved, sclerotized apically; with a small ring-like and a small spine-like apical processes; cornutus absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,548,1439]" box="[199,401,1341,1367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="288">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
